  <heading>UQINCP (vector)</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>Unsigned saturating increment vector by count of true predicate elements</brief>
    <description>
      <para>Counts the number of true elements in the source predicate and then uses the result to increment all destination vector elements. The results are saturated to the element unsigned integer range.</para>
      <para>The predicate size specifier may be omitted in assembler source code, but this is deprecated and will be prohibited in a future release of the architecture.</para>
    </description>
    <status>Green</status>
    <predicated>False</predicated>
    <takes_movprfx>True</takes_movprfx>
  </desc>
